Let’s dial back some of the more obvious “spooky” moments in this chapter and focus more on the feeling of normalcy—just like the guards might start their shifts believing everything is business as usual, so too should the reader. This creates a contrast that makes the little anomalies (the flickering lights, the odd creaks in the air conditioning) feel more unsettling when they do occur, since they’ll be harder to notice right away.

